China Hold Disarmament Talks With Neighboring Countries 
Chinese diplomatic and military experts held talks here today with
their counterparts from Russia, Kazakhstan, Kyrgzstan and Tadzhikistan
on reducing their military presence along their common borders.
The talks, the 19th round of its kind, were held in a friendly, frank
and pragmatic atmosphere.
They agreed that the next round of such talks will be held in Beijing
in August or September this year.
During their stay in Moscow, Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Alexandr
Panov met with the Chinese delegation.
